			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Worldwide Executive of Music, Activision, Inc.</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">As Worldwide Executive of Music at Activision, Inc., Tim Riley directs all activities concerning the integration of music into the company’s games and aggressively seeks opportunities to expand Activision’s alliances with record labels around the world.  With more than 12 years of experience in the music industry and an extensive background in A&R, music supervision and music licensing, Riley has brought established acts such as The Clash, The Doors, Johnny Cash, Frank Sinatra, Metallica, Snoop Dogg, Outkast, and countless others to Activision’s games. Riley has supervised critically-acclaimed and award-winning soundtracks including Tony Hawk’s Underground which was honored with the first ever MTV Video Music Award for “Best Soundtrack for a Video Game” in August 2004.
Prior to joining Activision, Riley was a founding partner of Westies Music where he supervised music direction for action sports films and video games.</span></td>
